<headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 19 at 1:52PM EDT  by NWS Raleigh</headline>
<description>...A strong thunderstorm will impact portions of Anson, southern
Montgomery, northwestern Richmond and southeastern Stanly Counties
through 300 PM EDT...
At 152 PM EDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Wadesboro, moving northeast at 25 mph.
HAZARD...Winds in excess of 40 mph.
SOURCE...Radar indicated.
IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects.
Locations impacted include...
Wadesboro, Troy, Biscoe, Ansonville, Polkton, Norwood, Oakboro, Mount
Gilead, Ellerbe and Candor.
MAX HAIL SIZE...0.00 IN
MAX WIND GUST...40 MPH</description>
<instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.
Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
